deck: Rock Lee's Seishun Full Power Ninden is the first official spin-off manga series based upon Masashi Kishimoto's original NARUTO series. Rock Lee is a young ninja who can't use ninjutsu but fights on to follow his dreams through training and his will.
description:
Proper Japanese Title: ロック・リーの青春フルパワー忍伝 (Rokku Rī no Seishun Furupowā Ninden)

Rock Lee Seishun Fullpower Ninden is a gag-spinoff of Masashi Kishimoto's Naruto manga, originally serialized in Saikyou Jump, that stars Rock Lee and others in chibi design. This series is written and illustrated by Kenji Taira, and began publication in Shueisha's Super Strong Jump magazine on December 2010.
name: Rock Lee's Seishun Full Power Ninden

description: The Perfect Memory Volume is aimed at comic collectors and series fans. Each issue provides synopsis and artist commentary for roughly 25 issues of the main storyline and a few of the one-shots. Also provided are an issue checklist for the issues mentioned, and some basic character/equipment/concept profiles. This volume covers the original 4-issue Mangazine series, the 4-issue B&W series, the 50-issue B&W Volume 1, and up through issue #75 of the color Volume 2 along with some early one-shots.
name: Gold Digger: Perfect Memory
